ject, and offers a clear and practical description of the various levels of organization.Themes are - Planning steps from basic evaluation to handing over the keys, - Project participants (including the authorities, specialized planners, construction firms, etc.), - Organizing the plan (sequence, what’s needed when?, work organization, documentation), - Coordination of the participants.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aArchitectural studies. 4aBasics. 4aBuilding projects. 4aPlanning process. 4aProject planning. 4aTextbook architecture. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBASICS ONLINE PACKAGE ENGLISHz978303561170008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Architecture, Design and Arts 2000 - 2014z9783110635690oZDB-23-GAA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Art and Architecture 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062112908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z97831102385700 cEPUBz97830356130320 cprintz978376438469240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978303561290540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783035612905423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783035612905/original  a978-3-0356-1170-0  BASICS ONLINE PACKAGE ENGLISH  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-062112-9  DGBA Backlist Art and Architecture 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GAAc2000d2014